<book>
   <bookTitle>Compiler Construction</bookTitle>
   <heading>Scanning and Parsing</heading>
   <p>
      <authorsRef refid="dragonBook"/>
in <emph>their <emph>highly popular</emph>
textbook on compiler construction</emph>
      <ref refid="dragonBook"/>
introduce
<list>
         <li>scanning and</li>
         <li>parsing</li>
      </list>
as the first two phases in compiler construction.<fn>The other
three phases are <list>
            <li>semantic analysis,</li>
            <li>code
generation, and</li>
            <li>code optimization.</li>
         </list>
      </fn>
   </p>
   <p>
      <authorsRef refid="loomBook"/>
      <ref refid="loomBook"/>
provide the theoretical foundation for scanning and parsing.</p>
   <p>In <ref refid="laterPhasesCh"/>
we examine the later phases.</p>
